3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Gate.io calculates SUI/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC based on the premium between perpetual and index prices. Long positions pay short positions when funding is positive, reflecting market bullishness. The exchange uses a dampening mechanism to prevent extreme rates, typically capping at ±2% per funding period. Position holders at settlement time automatically pay or receive funding based on their position size and the prevailing rate."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SUI","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI's mid-tier volume and L1 token dynamics create regular funding rate imbalances suitable for arbitrage strategies. The token's correlation with broader DeFi trends and ecosystem announcements generates predictable funding patterns. Gate.io's position as a major venue for SUI derivatives ensures sufficient liquidity for meaningful arbitrage positions."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI/USDT funding rates on Gate.io typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during ecosystem milestones and DeFi protocol launches. The pair shows increased funding volatility around major network upgrades and partnership announcements. Weekend periods often exhibit lower funding rates due to reduced retail participation. Monthly analysis reveals funding tends to spike during quarter-end when institutional rebalancing creates directional pressure."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Optimal arbitrage windows occur when SUI funding rates exceed 0.15% while maintaining negative rates on competing exchanges like Binance or OKX. Gate.io's 0.015% maker fees allow profitable arbitrage even on moderate funding differentials above 0.08%. Cross-exchange arbitrage requires monitoring SUI spot price differences, as Gate.io occasionally trades at slight premiums during high demand periods. Automated strategies should account for the 8-hour settlement cycle and position sizing based on available margin across exchanges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Position Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SUI's price volatility can exceed 10% intraday, requiring careful position sizing to avoid liquidation during adverse moves. Gate.io's margin requirements for SUI perpetuals typically range from 5-10% depending on position size and market conditions. Flash crashes in the broader L1 sector can trigger rapid funding rate reversals, making stop-loss management crucial. Regulatory developments affecting L1 blockchains pose additional tail risk that can impact both spot prices and funding dynamics simultaneously."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical SUI/USDT funding rates on Gate.io?","answer":"SUI/USDT funding rates on Gate.io typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per 8-hour period. During ecosystem developments or strong market trends, rates can reach the exchange's ±2% caps, though this occurs infrequently."},{"question":"How does Gate.io's SUI perpetual compare to other exchanges?","answer":"Gate.io often maintains competitive SUI funding rates due to its broad altcoin user base and strong Asian market presence. The exchange's 8-hour funding cycle aligns with major competitors, facilitating cross-exchange arbitrage strategies."},{"question":"What margin requirements apply to SUI perpetuals on Gate.io?","answer":"Gate.io requires 5-10% initial margin for SUI/USDT perpetuals depending on position size. Maintenance margin is typically 2.5-5%, with larger positions facing higher requirements due to SUI's volatility classification."},{"question":"When do SUI funding rate arbitrage opportunities peak?","answer":"Peak opportunities often occur during SUI ecosystem announcements, DeFi protocol launches, or broader L1 sector rotations. Friday afternoons and Monday mornings also show increased funding rate dispersion across exchanges due to weekend position adjustments."}]}]
